977504530a9869c97534b0bd67b9c40901f597d8a87e6114e21d7a379","event_uuid":"87ef1799-4abb-453e-a482-ce8c61effc70","position":{"commit_sha":"b2b83dcb0bbb5c91c25677ad8c79416cee99f9eb","position":"1784443841920194001-87ef1799-4abb-453e-a482-ce8c61effc70"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"66953232fe88df48a6d8c92dca256172cbc7315478c3480b2b7a95522d678c48","event_uuid":"98ec5e9e-a894-4e8f-87f2-9aeeaf02c6d9","position":{"commit_sha":"93b431db73aeb4df773050ff8af4a9703f076cfe","position":"1784443964586861169-98ec5e9e-a894-4e8f-87f2-9aeeaf02c6d9"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"6e3fbad8-702f-4987-ad70-cc88122eea43","comments":[],"created_at":1784416757443607001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"409fc362-98cf-45b9-a50d-f6bbf6b1f4a6","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"c085-6d11-d68d-422a"},{"link_uuid":"d986c05b-55f1-4633-a92a-59bdee262d50","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"8bc5-9c76-95f3-465e"}],"description":"## What\nRead-only derivations over the existing gate sidecars for gate-economics + env-diagnosis metrics: an LLM cost proxy (`llm_calls`, latency) from the plan/code-review sidecars, cost-per-accepted-change, first-pass verification, and env-diagnosis intervals (`gate_error_v1` ERROR → next PASS). All read-only; nothing is written.\n\n## Data-access ground truth (the plan is built on this)\n- **Only `REVIEW_RESULT` (`plan_review_result_v2`) carries a `metrics` block** — `{det_ms, llm_ms, total_ms, llm_calls, claim_path}` (`plan_review/sidecar.py:496-497`). **`COMPLETION_VERDICT` carries NO metrics block** (verified in `completion_sidecar.py:182-219`; neither the pass nor fail branch has `llm_calls`). So all `llm_calls`/latency derivations read `REVIEW_RESULT.metrics` ONLY — the completion sidecar is used for the pass/fail *outcome*, never for cost.\n- **\"Accepted change\"** is defined precisely: a `completion_verifier_pass_v1` record (`SCHEMA_PASS`, `completion_sidecar.py:29`) on a ticket — i.e. the completion (close) gate PASSED. This is NOT a plan-review PASS (`plan_review_result_v2` with `verdict==\"PASS\"`), which only clears the *claim* gate and does not mean the ticket closed. The reader distinguishes the two by schema.\n- Sidecars are reducer-ignored. **This reader uses a single RAW ordered scan** of each ticket's `*-REVIEW_RESULT.json` and `*-COMPLETION_VERDICT.json` event files (resolve dir via `tracker_dir`+`resolve_ticket_dir_name`; sort by the ns-epoch filename prefix / `event_sort_key`; `json.load`; read `event[\"data\"]` + `event[\"timestamp\"]`). The schema-guarded helpers are NOT used for counting, because `latest_pass_record` returns only the single most-recent PASS (`completion_sidecar.py:137`) and `all_review_results` hard-filters to `plan_review_result_v1/v2` — neither can COUNT completion passes nor surface `gate_error_v1`. A record's kind is read off `data.schema` / `data.verdict`: `plan_review_result_v2` (verdict PASS/BLOCK/FAIL) with a `metrics` block; `completion_verifier_pass_v1` / `_fail_v1`; and `gate_error_v1` (verdict ERROR, carries a `gate` field). The raw scan sees ALL of them on the stream in order.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/metrics/sidecar_metrics.py` — new: reader over the sidecars, registered into `src/rebar/metrics/registry.py`.\n- `tests/unit/metrics/test_sidecar_metrics.py` — new.\n\n## Metric definitions\n- **llm_call_proxy / latency** — sum `REVIEW_RESULT.metrics.llm_calls` (and latency fields) over the range. `source=\"sidecar\"`.\n- **cost_per_accepted_change** — summed `REVIEW_RESULT.metrics.llm_calls` divided by the count of `completion_verifier_pass_v1` records (accepted closes) in range; returns `None` (→ `Unavailable`) when there are zero accepted closes (no division by zero).\n- **first_pass_verification** — fraction of tickets whose FIRST `COMPLETION_VERDICT` record is a `completion_verifier_pass_v1` (passed on the first verification attempt).\n- **first_pass_verification** — fraction of tickets whose FIRST `COMPLETION_VERDICT` record (oldest-first by filename order) is a `completion_verifier_pass_v1` (passed on the first close-verification attempt). Reads the raw COMPLETION_VERDICT files per ticket in chronological order and inspects the earliest one's schema.\n- **env_diagnosis_interval** — pair each `gate_error_v1` ERROR record with the next PASS record **for the SAME gate** on that ticket's stream. Because plan-review and code-review both write to `REVIEW_RESULT`, pairing matches on the ERROR record's `gate` field (`plan_review`/`code_review`/`completion`) against the next same-gate PASS (a `plan_review_result_v2`/code-review PASS for those gates, a `completion_verifier_pass_v1` for completion) — NOT merely the next PASS on the stream. The interval = PASS `timestamp` − ERROR `timestamp`; an ERROR with no following same-gate PASS is an open (unclosed) diagnosis interval.\n\n## Approach\nPure read-side derivations over sidecars that already persist per-run metrics, verdicts, and (via ticket 8bc5) the additive ERROR outcome. `confidence=\"high\"`; `is_authoritative(\"sidecar\")` is True. Nothing is written.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (real sidecar fixtures written to a temp store): cost-per-accepted-change over 3 REVIEW_RESULT runs (llm_calls 2+3+4=9) with 1 `completion_verifier_pass_v1` returns 9; with 0 accepted returns `None`. An ERROR record paired with a later PASS on the same ticket yields an interval equal to the fixture timestamp delta; an ERROR with no PASS yields an open interval.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/metrics/test_sidecar_metrics.py` passes: a `gate_error_v1` ERROR row paired with a later PASS on the same ticket yields a diagnosis-interval duration equal to the fixture timestamp delta (`assert dur == expected`).\n- [ ] cost_per_accepted_change over a fixture of 3 REVIEW_RESULT runs summing `llm_calls==9` with exactly 1 `completion_verifier_pass_v1` returns 9; a fixture with 0 accepted closes returns `None` (→ `Unavailable`, no ZeroDivisionError) — both asserted.\n- [ ] the cost derivations read `llm_calls` ONLY from `REVIEW_RESULT.metrics` (never from COMPLETION_VERDICT, which has none) — asserted by a fixture whose COMPLETION_VERDICT records carry no metrics yet cost is still computed from the REVIEW_RESULT runs.\n- [ ] `first_pass_verification` over a fixture of 3 tickets where 2 have their EARLIEST `COMPLETION_VERDICT` record as `completion_verifier_pass_v1` and 1 has an earliest `completion_verifier_fail_v1` returns 2/3 — asserted numerically (proves the oldest-first COMPLETION_VERDICT scan).\n- [ ] `env_diagnosis_interval` pairs a `gate_error_v1` ERROR (gate=`plan_review`) with the next `plan_review` PASS and NOT with an interleaved `completion` PASS on the same REVIEW_RESULT/COMPLETION_VERDICT streams — asserted (proves the gate-field match).\n- [ ] the metrics register into `src/rebar/metrics/registry.py` with `source=\"sidecar\"` (authoritative) — asserted.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/metrics/sidecar_metrics.py","reason":"gate-sidecar reader"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","8bc5-9c76-95f3-465e"],["depends_on","c085-6d11-d68d-422a"],["parent","86ac-086a-20ad-4327"]],"parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","parent_status_uuid":"01255ae0-9f4a-465d-9905-21626a9a34a1","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics"],"ticket_id":"3c07-27ac-4b61-47a3","ticket_type":"task","title":"Gate-sidecar reader (gate-economics + env-diagnosis metrics)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["54d65cf2-5967-42c4-91a4-78573b0bdcb4","41fb6d75-8202-4724-a79f-cfdb819c574f","409fc362-98cf-45b9-a50d-f6bbf6b1f4a6","d986c05b-55f1-4633-a92a-59bdee262d50","e97e1435-11b5-4cd3-ace7-9e9ea8ea511b","68475c3a-b708-4ee2-bd81-2abdc56a6e7d","874ced74-599c-4b33-954f-21b8c38c0cea","01255ae0-9f4a-465d-9905-21626a9a34a1","87ef1799-4abb-453e-a482-ce8c61effc70","98ec5e9e-a894-4e8f-87f2-9aeeaf02c6d9"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784443964586861170,"uuid":"2a2ffc04-d258-449c-aa81-93f11ad23fed"}